A woman escaped losing her leg by inches after she toppled onto the tracks in front of a moving train.

Had the train moved just a foot more the woman, who is in her 20s, would probably have lost her leg in the incident at Birmingham New Street station and could have been killed. 

She was found laid on her back between the tracks and the wall of the platform, with her left leg bent up behind her. 

