The woman fell onto the tracks at about 6pm, as the 5.31pm Walsall to Wolverhampton train arrived at the platform. She was found with her left leg was bent back with her thigh against her body and her calf against the train. 

Paramedics found she was not seriously injured but she was taken to Birmingham City Hospital for further checks.  

London Midland is investigating the incident in conjunction with Network Rail. 

